  "text": "Note that in general cases the perfect secrecy is not achievable. Since in our first theorem U Z , B3C E5 approximates to zero and is not zero exactly. Also in the second theorem we have shown when the null message is eliminated from the alphabet G, the perfect secrecy can be achievable and this postulate doesn't conflict with the first proof in [CITATION_1] .",
